  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_4' aria-label=\" Sri Prasanta Kumar Pal & Ors versus The State of West Bengal & Ors pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('4','2025','2025_4_2606_2611','2025INSC783'); ><font size='4'> <strong>SRI PRASANTA KUMAR PAL & ORS<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>THE STATE OF WEST BENGAL & ORS </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 4 S.C.R. 2606</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 783</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010007272025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : RAJESH BINDAL, N KOTISWAR SINGH</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the observation of the Revenue Officer, as prima facie accepted by the High Court that the transaction of gift deed dated 07.12.1967 was a Benami transaction is totally erroneous as the amendment (2nd and 3rd Amendment in the West Bengal Land into effect almost two decades after registered gift deed was executed. Headnotes&dagger; West Bengal Land Reforms Act, 1955 &ndash; 2nd Amendment (came into force on 07.08.1969) and 3rd Amendment (came into force on 12.05.1989) &ndash; s.14T(3) r/w ss.14M, 14T (8) &amp; (9) &amp; 14S &ndash;<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 08-04-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 5078/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2025','2025_4_2606_2611','2025INSC783','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('4','2